Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art showing the outlines of a giraffe and an antelope, both upright and facing right. The giraffe is on the left with a naturalistic outline and no coat pattern markings and antelope is on the right, on the other side of a natural vertical divide in the rock, with a long, corpulent body, long tapered tail, small head and short legs (unfinished?); the faint wavy horns suggest a gracile antelope – likely a gazelle. Western Desert, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
